                            <comment id="14470787" author="mikevines" created="Fri, 4 Feb 2011 11:20:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to know your thoughts on this, so I know if it is something that will be addressed in a future Groovy build, or if it is something I need to deal with in my application.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Mike&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14479448" author="paulk" created="Sat, 5 Feb 2011 01:10:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed patch attached to remove dependency - if ivy jar not in classpath you won&apos;t get ivy notifications - but in that case you wouldn&apos;t have any ivy functionality, i.e. no @Grab at all&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14470720" author="guillaume" created="Sat, 5 Feb 2011 13:43:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch looks elegant to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
